   "source": [
    "# Interview Prep: 24 - FinOps & Cost Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "At a certain scale, the Cloud Bill becomes as important as the Latency. This notebook covers how to design systems that are both high-performing and cost-efficient.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The Hidden Cost: Data Egress\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"We are moving 100PB of data between an AWS region in the US and one in Europe. What is the primary bottleneck?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Answer**: **Cost (Egress Fees)**. \n",
    "- Cloud providers often allow \"Data In\" for free but charge heavily for \"Data Out\" (Egress).\n",
    "- **Optimization**: Use **Compression** before transit, and keep data within the same availability zone (AZ) where possible.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Compute Economics: Spot vs. Reserved\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"How can we run a massive image processing job for 80% less cost than our current setup?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Answer**: **Spot Instances**.\n",
    "- Spot instances are "spare capacity" sold at a massive discount, but the cloud provider can take them back with 2 minutes notice.\n",
    "- **Architecture**: The application must be **Stateless** and support **Check-pointing**. If an instance is killed, another one picks up from the last saved state.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Storage Tiering (S3 Logic)\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Interview Question**: \"We have 1 trillion log files. We rarely look at them, but we must keep them for 7 years for compliance. How do we store them?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Answer**: **Archive Tiering** (e.g., AWS Glacier Deep Archive).\n",
    "- **Standard**: $0.023/GB. Instant access.\n",
    "- **Glacier Deep Archive**: $0.00099/GB. Retrieval takes 12-48 hours.\n",
    "- **Result**: Over 95% cost reduction for long-term storage.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Coding Scenario: Estimating Cache Cost\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task**: Calculate the monthly cost of a 100GB Redis cache vs. 10TB of S3 storage to decide if we should cache more or read more from disk.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_monthly_bill(storage_gb, price_per_gb):\n",
    "    return storage_gb * price_per_gb\n",
    "\n",
    "redis_cost = calculate_monthly_bill(100, 0.15)  # $15/month for RAM\n",
    "s3_cost = calculate_monthly_bill(10000, 0.023)  # $230/month for Disk\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Redis (RAM): ${redis_cost}\")\n",
    "print(f\"S3 (Disk): ${s3_cost}\")\n",
    "print(\"Recommendation: Caching is significantly cheaper than massive disk scans if data is accessed frequently.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. FinOps Summary\n",
    "- **Compute**: Spot Instances for batch, Reserved for baseline.\n",
    "- **Networking**: Avoid cross-region egress; use private endpoints.\n",
    "- **Review**: Use \"Cost Explorer\" to find orphaned resources (idle load balancers, unattached volumes).\n",
    "---"
   ]
  }
 ],
